"cat": "knowledge",
"id": "audit-and-change-log",
"title": "Audit & Change Log Standard",
"summary": "Normative guidance for the project's **durable, committed, history-as-knowledge** record: an append-only **audit log** of every meaningful prompt, skill, and script, and a curated **change log** of every meaningful design decision. It…",
"path": "pack/knowledge/audit-and-change-log.md",
"kind": "knowledge",
"text": "audit & change log standard normative guidance for the project's **durable, committed, history-as-knowledge** record: an append-only **audit log** of every meaningful prompt, skill, and script, and a curated **change log** of every meaningful design decision. it governs how every skill records what it did, how the four design-shaping skills capture decisions, how both feed the knowledge graph, and how a human or a fresh agent session reads the project's own past. the knowledge visualization standard (`knowledge-visualization.md`) governs the artifact graph; this document governs the **activity and decision history** that runs alongside it. the viewer and the `/auditlog` cli render it; the script bundle (`scripts/audit-log.py`) is the only tool that writes it. audit & change log standard 0. the two logs (one bundle) 1. the audit-log entry schema 2. the audit mandate — every skill writes to the log 3. the change mandate — capturing meaningful decisions 4. knowledge-graph & session-history integration 5. the viewer and the cli 6. self-verification checklist 7. references # audit & change log standard *normative guidance for the project's **durable, committed, history-as-knowledge** record: an append-only **audit log** of every meaningful prompt, skill, and script, and a curated **change log** of every meaningful design decision. it governs how every skill records what it did, how the four design-shaping skills capture decisions, how both feed the knowledge graph, and how a human or a fresh agent session reads the project's own past. the knowledge visualization standard (`knowledge-visualization.md`) governs the artifact graph; this document governs the **activity and decision history** that runs alongside it. the viewer and the `/auditlog` cli render it; the script bundle (`scripts/audit-log.py`) is the only tool that writes it.* normative keywords (**must**, **should**, **may**, **must not**) follow rfc 2119. the governing idea: **a coding session's reasoning is the most valuable thing it produces and the first thing lost when the session ends.** an agent's session store is ephemeral and private to that session; the next copilot or claude code session starts blind to it. so the project keeps its *own* committed memory of what was prompted, what was done, and what was decided — in plain append-only files that travel with the repo. the audit log answers *\"what has happened here?\"*; the change log answers *\"what was decided, and why?\"*. together they make work **compound across sessions** instead of evaporating. --- ## 0. the two logs (one bundle) | file | what it is | written by | shape | |---|---|---|---| | `docs/audit/audit-log.jsonl` | **audit log** — every meaningful prompt / skill run / script / action | every skill (audit mandate, §2) + the `/auditlog` skill | append-only jsonl | | `docs/audit/change-log.jsonl` | **change log** — every meaningful design decision / change | the four design-shaping skills + discerned changes (change mandate, §3) | append-only jsonl | | `docs/audit/audit-data.js` | **derived** `window.audit_data` for the viewer (loadable over `file://`) | `audit-log.py` regenerates it on every write | derived — never hand-edited | | `docs/audit/index.html` | the **interactive viewer** (timeline · search · toggle audit/changes) | self-bootstrapped from `templates/audit-explorer.template.html` | regenerated; never hand-edited | | `docs/audit/audit-log.md` | the **knowledge-graph hub node** (frontmatter; §4) | the skill that first creates the bundle | a graph artifact (`type: doc`) | **al0 — jsonl is the source of truth; the js is derived.** the two `*.jsonl` files are the canonical record — append-only, one json object per line, so each session adds lines and git diffs stay clean (the same pattern as `docs/health-history.jsonl`). `audit-data.js` and `index.html` are **derived projections** regenerated by `audit-log.py`; where they disagree with the jsonl, the jsonl wins and is re-rendered. nothing hand-edits the derived files. **al0.1 — all writes go through the script bundle.** the audit and change logs are written **only** via `docs/ai-forward-pack/scripts/audit-log.py` (`append`, `change`, `import`), never by hand-appending json or generating an ad-hoc script at prompt time — exactly as graph mechanics go only through `docs-graph.py` (v18). the script assigns the id, stamps the time, escapes the content for the viewer, and re-renders in one step. --- ## 1. the audit-log entry schema each audit entry records one meaningful action. the five **required** fields are the user-facing minimum; the rest are the enrichment that makes the log searchable, graph-linked, and useful to a future session. ```json { \"id\": \"al-0007\", // assigned by the script (al-nnnn), the redo/reference key \"shortname\": \"design-gateway\", // required — a short human label \"datetime\": \"2026-06-27t14:28:09z\", // required — iso-8601 utc (auto if omitted) \"session\": \"2dbe541d-…\", // required — the session id (links to session history) \"prompt\": \"run /design on the payment gateway…\", // required — the prompt / command, verbatim \"summary\": \"produced docs/design/payment-gateway.md; 3 failure modes dispositioned.\", // required — what the result was \"kind\": \"skill\", // skill|command|script|prompt|commit|manual|session-import \"skill\": \"design\", // the skill that ran, if any \"tool\": \"copilot cli\", // the agent/tool that ran it \"actor\": \"@handle\", // who initiated it (optional) \"artifacts\": [\"docs/design/payment-gateway.md\"], // files created/changed — graph links (§4) \"tags\": [\"payments\", \"resilience\"], // keywords for search \"outcome\": \"success\", // success|partial|failed|blocked \"change\": \"cl-0003\", // link to a change-log entry, when this action was also a decision \"git\": { \"sha\": \"…\", \"short\": \"…\", \"branch\": \"main\", \"pushed\": true } // optional, via --git } ``` **al1 — the five required fields.** every audit entry **must** carry `shortname`, `datetime`, `session`, `prompt`, and `summary`. the `prompt` is…"
